The discontinued bird nest with seeds is an old variant of the seed nest that was obtainable before the release of the Farming Guild. All nests previously obtained remained in banks and inventories, and all new nests obtained can now reward dragonfruit, celastrus, and redwood tree seeds. This change was made to prevent players from obtaining large quantities of the new seeds immediately upon release of the content.

This variant of bird nest can be seen during in Cyrisus's bank during Dream Mentor, but it can't be removed from the bank interface.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
7 July 2021
(update)

The item rotation is updated to make it more clear whether bird nests are empty or contain seeds.

10 January 2019
(update)

This variant of seed nest is discontinued and replaced with the current variant. Previously obtained nests may still exist in inventories and banks.

20 September 2018
(update)

The item's value was increased from 20 to 453 so that it would appear above logs when on the ground.

22 March 2018
(update)

The item's value was increased from 1 to 20.

14 April 2016
(update)

The message received when causing a bird's nest to fall whilst woodcutting is now displayed in red.

27 March 2014
(update | poll)

Can now be received as a drop when chopping the log left by a slain Ent.
